subSubSection.paragraph:
Food and Feeding.
About one-half (48-1%) of diet of Liechtenstein’s Pine Vole consists of green dicotyledonous plants, in particular of buttercups (
Ranunculaceae
), pinks (
Caryophyllaceae
), heathers (
Ericaceae
), and dogbanes (
Apocynaceae
). Close to one-tenth (9-3%) of the diet consists of flowers, seeds, fruits, fungi, and lichens. Grasses are not favored.
